25:49.606 --> 25:56.178
As you travel, you're going to encounter old habits, you're going to encounter temptations, things that need to be dealt with.

25:56.866 --> 26:03.478
Not only that, the Bible tells us there's a spiritual enemy who opposes all that is holy and will try to trip us up.

26:04.680 --> 26:08.887
And I'm guessing that most of us here are on that side of the Jordan.

26:10.209 --> 26:14.176
We have taken the step of faith to follow Jesus.

26:16.300 --> 26:17.522
And now we're in the fight.

26:18.914 --> 26:24.902
It was near the end of World War II that Allied forces were closing in on the final stages of the Pacific conflict.

26:24.963 --> 26:27.486
And for all intents, the war was won.

26:28.147 --> 26:33.475
Japan was on the ropes, and it was just a matter of time really until final victory was declared.

26:34.656 --> 26:37.981
But the fight was still ongoing, and it was fierce.

26:39.363 --> 26:44.370
Okinawa was one of the bloodiest battles, though it didn't seem so at first.

26:45.122 --> 26:49.147
When Marines landed on the beaches of Okinawa, they met almost no resistance.

26:49.207 --> 26:55.495
In fact, in the first 24 hours, they covered a distance that they had anticipated was going to require days of fighting.

26:56.476 --> 27:01.923
And they began to think that the enemy was on the run, but they were wrong.

27:02.944 --> 27:09.953
The enemy was simply hiding underground and had camouflage and trench positions behind the ridges.

27:11.354 --> 27:14.258
And so many positions didn't look difficult at all.

27:15.010 --> 27:16.372
Like Sugarloaf Hill.

27:17.574 --> 27:19.376
Sugarloaf was one of three small hills.

27:19.396 --> 27:22.120
There was half moon, horseshoe, and sugarloaf.

27:22.180 --> 27:25.525
And sugarloaf was only 230 feet above sea level.

27:26.467 --> 27:32.275
And actually, when you took in this surrounding terrain, it was only 50 feet higher than the terrain around it.

27:34.078 --> 27:34.939
How hard could it be?

27:37.463 --> 27:39.886
Well, sugarloaf, let me just read this to you.

27:40.067 --> 27:42.450
Sugarloaf was honeycomb with any positions.

27:42.914 --> 27:45.837
Any one of the three hills could be defended by any of the others.

27:46.738 --> 27:50.882
Interlocking fields of fire from each hill protected the slopes and approaches of the others.

27:51.843 --> 27:59.930
Preregistered artillery spots have been gridded all over Sugar Loaf's terrain, allowing any step by Marines to come under withering artillery fire.

28:01.192 --> 28:05.596
Machine gun positions that the Marines had never seen before lined half moon and horseshoe.

28:06.397 --> 28:11.922
While the real beast, Sugar Loaf, was pockmarked with concrete, reverse slope positions

28:12.290 --> 28:16.175
that would have to be eliminated one by one by hand.

28:18.177 --> 28:18.938
Well, you know the history.

28:20.019 --> 28:24.264
The Marines did eventually take Sugarloaf Hill, but it wasn't easy.

28:25.586 --> 28:28.950
And I would submit to you, there are battles in the Christian life that are like that as well.

28:30.311 --> 28:39.282
